; UNSAT: (x XOR y) != (x + y) AND (x AND y) == 0 for 12-bit x, y
; When AND(x,y)==0, there are no carries, so XOR == ADD always.
; Requiring XOR != ADD with AND==0 is impossible.
; Domain: 4096^2 = 16M — tests multi-variable blast
; Expected: UNSAT
1 sort bitvec 12
2 sort bitvec 1
3 input 1 x
4 input 1 y
5 xor 1 3 4
6 add 1 3 4
7 neq 2 5 6
8 and 1 3 4
9 zero 1
10 eq 2 8 9
11 and 2 7 10
12 bad 11
